The nursery school is also part of offices that included architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint of Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected him to also house a mini kindergarten with everything he needs - color walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, the children of Arch. design employees can go there.
The Arch. Design. architectural project company, whose workshops produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini-maternity business school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially the age to make children, and it was important that women architects and project leaders could quickly return to work.
At the same time as reduced-time employment contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Manufacturers and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design.eu who imagined this nursery school and with the support of management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-maternal school is financed through the European Social Fund through the operational programme of human resources and the State budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to funding allocations (up to 2.8 million Czech kroner) they were able to purchase equipment and appliances and after two years provide qualified personnel and start-up.
After using the funding endowment (two years) Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini nursery school on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and it was the Economy rating company that helped make the application for staffing.
Care for children is provided by qualified staff, a nurse and a kindergarten teacher attend to children all day. Children can go to kindergarten without age limitations, but they are over three years old for most.
Since it is a "mini nursery school" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace themselves.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although he is involved in individual care and education, the programme of the mini-maternal school is comparable to that of pre-school education.
Children do not only play, but quality education is also provided - from the beginning to preparation for school benches English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and do not have the stress of a delay to pick up the children in a school away from the parents' workplace.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design.s is thus registered among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and who are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens HR marketing.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look inside Gaudi.
The cough resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the stairway with a spine of dinosaur and the balconies with open fish mouths.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic forms, the house received from the premises the nickname of House in bone.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaic, facade recalling scales and everywhere present curves, this is all ypic for the Art Nouveau d'Antoni Gaudi.
The front façade of the house unfolds its dream lines, its pleasant colors and textures that remind nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, rhythm and order thought with precision.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, balustrades, decorative elements of the doors, eyelet and lamelles.
The Battlo house that stands in the Eixample district in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at number. 43, was born from the construction of a house of 1877 by architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
Reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old construction and the construction of another brand new but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But Casa Battlo's idea as a house with multiple dwellings was not thought of by Gaudi alone.
Architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that the decorations were born for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade.
Other artists and creators also worked for the façade.
The common work for the plans of Casa Battlo began with successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The locals nicknamed the house hot just after its finishing because of its organic forms "the House in bone".
Others, in view of the specific window opening mechanism, called it "the house that dances".
It is said that at the top of the building there is a sword similar to that of Saint Georges the patron of Catalonia.
Other elements of sculpture of the construction contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its time of central heating, with vents of ventilation and typical fireplaces.
Their 45-degree inclination seems odd.
During the creation of Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the directives for the construction of then and did not allow itself to be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained a permit from the city to build, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finishing the municipal council was horrified and demanded modifications.
For example, the members of the municipal council did not like the building pillars to be built on the public sidewalk.
There was never a change, but on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo asked (and got satisfaction) for permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and in the third a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented at a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase that leads to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of space binding.
The common part can be fully connected by opening the doors of the lounges and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi has received in addition to new facades a non-traditional roof and two additional floors.
Gaudi's play with light is also impressive, blue and white glazed tiles with which is decorated the inner courtyard and with light wells.
The two-colored game gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was simply enough to bet on the principle that white reflects more than dark which, on the contrary, absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house, which was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund, may be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued the visits because they found it to be a lucrative company and expanded the field of visits to the common spaces and attic including the terraces of toast.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist card holders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the entry price in the other buildings of Gaudi in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
